                   <div class="txtNew" data-packed="true" id="comp-ifmduswg" style="top:93px;bottom:;left:52px;right:;width:734px;height:auto;position:absolute">
                    <h6 class="font_6" style="font-size:18px; text-align:center;">
                     <span style="font-size:18px;">
                      Harley Owners Group
                     </span>
                     <br/>
                    </h6>
                    <h5 class="font_5" style="font-size:18px; text-align:justify;">
                     <span style="font-size:18px;">
                      Harley-Davidsonestablished the Harley Owners Groupin 1983 in response to a growing desire by Harley riders for an organised way to share their passion and show their pride. By 1985, 49 local chapters had sprouted around the United States, with a total membership of 60,000. Rapid growth continued into the 1990s, and in 1991 H.O.G.officially went international, with the first official European H.O.G.rally in Cheltenham, England. Worldwide membership numbered 151,600, with 685 local chapters. As the '90s continued, H.O.G. hysteria spread into Asia, including new chapters in Singapore and Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. By 1999, worldwide membership had hit the half-million mark, and the number of local chapters totalled 1,157. Today, almost one million members make H.O.G. the largest factory-sponsored motorcycle organisation in the world, and it shows absolutely no signs of slowing down. What does the future hold? No one can say for sure, but from here the road ahead looks long, wide open, winding, and scenic with lots of new friends to make along the way. So why notJoin H.O.G.nowand come explore it with us? We promise you'll enjoy the ride.
                     </span>
                    </h5>
                    <h5 class="font_5" style="font-size:18px; text-align:justify;">
                    </h5>
                    <h5 class="font_5" style="font-size:18px; text-align:justify;">
                     <span style="font-size:18px;">
                      Male and female riders of Harley-Davidson Motorcycles are encouragedto join and experience the H.O.G.family and lifestyle.
                     </span>
                    </h5>
                    <h5 class="font_5" style="font-size:18px; text-align:justify;">
                    </h5>
                    <h5 class="font_5" style="font-size:18px; text-align:justify;">
                     <span style="font-size:18px;">
                      The Perth Chapter organise and runregular social events and rides including a Saturday "Intro Ride" where you can come along for a short and smallgroup ride followed by aBBQ back at Frasers to see if you would like to join us!
                     </span>
                    </h5>
                   </div>

The members of LOH sponsor activities that both ladies and men can participate in. organised way to share their passion and show their pride. By 1985, 49 local chapters had sprouted around the United States, with a total membership of 60,000. Rapid growth continued into the 1990s, and in 1991 H.O.G.&reg;&nbsp;officially went international, with the first official European H.O.G.&reg;&nbsp;rally in Cheltenham, England. Worldwide membership numbered 151,600, with 685 local chapters. As the &#39;90s continued, H.O.G.&reg; hysteria spread into Asia, including new chapters in Singapore and Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. The members can be either a rider&nbsp;or a passenger as&nbsp;long as they are willing to participate in&nbsp;little or much.<\/span><\/span><\/h6>\n\n<h5 class=\"font_5\" style=\"font-size:25px; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:25px\"><span style=\"font-family:din-next-w01-light,din-next-w02-light,din-next-w10-light,sans-serif\">LOH promotes participation by ladies in the world of Harley-Davidson. Sometimes sports activities can become dominated by men&nbsp;ie basketball, football, orienteering, mountain climbing, track, need I say more. Since H.O.G.&reg; is all about just having family fun, the auxiliary group LOH was formed to provide an avenue for the ladies. Contact your local H.O.G.&reg; Chapter for details on joining the chapter.
